Mesosoma (
Fig. 45
) shorter than metasoma. Propodeum (
Fig. 44
) with fine submedian lines often hardly visible. Fore wing (
Fig. 46
) 3.5–3.8 × as long as wide; longest marginal seta about 0.22–0.27 × maximum wing width. Fore wing disc slightly infumate throughout, bare behind submarginal vein and setose elsewhere. Hind wing 28–29 × as long as wide; disc bare except for rows of setae along margins and a few additional setae at apex, slightly infumate; longest marginal seta 3.0– 3.7 × maximum wing width.

Metasoma (
Fig. 45
) with petiole wider than long. Ovipositor occupying 0.7–0.9 × length of gaster, a little exserted beyond its apex (by at most 0.1 × own length); ovipositor length: mesotibia length ratio 1.3–1.9 : 1 .
